Changelog
=========

Version 1.3beta

Adding more default values to the Measurement object in sensor.py.
Most use cases only need to pass the Trig Pin and Echo Pin

Default values are
unit = 'metric'
temperature = <celcius value>
round_to = 1

Default usage
-------------
sensor.Measurement(trig_pin, echo_pin)


Alternative usage
-----------------
sensor.Measurement(trig_pin, echo_pin, temperature=68, unit='imperial', round_to=3)



Version 1.2.0
Python 3 compatibility

Version 1.1.4
Allow changing the default sample size from 11 to a user defined value.  Default
remains 11 unless otherwise specified.


Version 1.1.3
Cleanup only GPIO pins being used in sensor.py

Version 1.1.2 
Improved error handling in sensor.py

Version 1.1.1
All functions in sensor.py now methods of Measurement class

Version 1.1.0
Module expanded to allow metric or imperial readings.
See examples/examples.py for usage

Version 1.0.3
Small change to example script depth.py

Version 1.0.2
-Fix bug introduced with version 0.5.11 of RPi.GPIO
